               <head>Two Persian treatises and one in Arabic</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009123573 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083116">
                  <summary>Two Persian treatises and one in Arabic, on geomancy, medicine, and general good health. Other contents: f. 1r, geomantic divination markings, talismanic figures; 2r, magic squares, talismanic formulae, formula for sleepless infants, verses, etc.; 89v, description of the hoopoe, in semi-shikasta nasta‘līq; 90r, the qualities of a cock, in the same hand as the last; 104r, an imprecation against the idols of Quraysh, in the same hand as text 3; nine bayts of verse addressed to Imam Ḥasan, and three to Fāṭima, in a later hand. Purchased from A Kazzaz, 11 March 2005. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85054121" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16175-item1">
                     <locus from="2v" to="21v">ff. 2v-21v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise on geomancy, in 12 chapters (bāb), each comprising numerous sections (faṣls). As the title given in the preface show, this work is putatively derived from the teachings of the Prophets <persName key="person_30330876" role="ant">Daniel</persName> and <persName key="person_291480234" role="ant">Idrīs</persName> (here perhaps identified with Hermes Trismegistos). The present copy is incomplete: it contains several of the faṣls comprising the first bāb. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Undated: ca. 12th/18th century. </p>
                        <p>Naskhī. 18 lines. Tables with geomantic symbols.  172 x 116 mm.; text area 120 x 62 mm.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22106">Risālah-'ī az asrār-i ʿulūm-i muʿjizah-'i Ḥaz̤rat-i Dāniyāl va Idr̛īs</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22106">رساله اى از اسرار علوم معجزهٔ حضرت دانيال و ادريس</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083117" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Or_16175-item2">
                     <locus from="22r" to="89v">ff. 22r-89v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7338">Muḥammad ʿAlī Ṭabāṭabāʾī Iṣfahānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7338">محمّد على طباطبائى اصفهانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22110">Rāḥat al-insān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22110">راحة الانسان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise on simple and compound remedies. By Muḥammad ‘Alī Ṭabāṭabā’ī Iṣfahānī (ca. 11th/17th century). Munzavī, in FNKhF I p. 543, records only one other copy (Tehran University, Faculty of Medicine MS. 114/1). The present manuscript must be incomplete at the end, but contains marginalia that include corrections as well as annotations, and so was presumably checked against another.</p>
                        <p>Undated: ca. 12th/18th century. </p>
                        <p>Clear naskhī. 15 lines. Red headings. 172 x 116 mm.; text area 128 x 64 mm.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85101540" n="3" xml:id="Uk_Or_16175-item3">
                     <locus from="90v" to="104r">ff. 90v-104r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>A medical tract in Arabic, on the maintenance of good health through correct food, drink and medicines. This work is implausibly attributed to ‘Alī ibn Mūsà al-Riżā, Ninth Imam of the Shī‘a. See Brockelmann, GAL S I, pp. 318-9. Several Persian translations exist in manuscript: see Munzavī, FNKhF I, pp. 498-501.</p>
                        <p>Undated: ca. 12th/18th century. Clear naskhī. 15 lines. Text area 115 x 60 mm. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8693">al-Risālat al-Z̲ahabīyah fī al-ṭibb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8693">الرّسالة الذّهبيّه فى الطّبّ</title>
                  </msItem>
